  "prompt": "What is the procedure to check your PF balance?",
  "response": "To check your PF (Provident Fund) balance, you can follow these methods:\n\n1. EPFO Portal (Online Method):\n- Visit the official EPFO website (www.epfindia.gov.in)\n- Click on \"Our Services\"\n- Select \"Member Passbook\"\n- Enter UAN (Universal Account Number)\n- Enter password\n- View your PF balance\n\n2. UMANG Mobile App:\n- Download UMANG app\n- Register/login\n- Select EPFO services\n- Enter UAN and password\n- Check balance\n\n3. Missed Call/SMS Service:\n- Give a missed call to 011-22901406 from registered mobile number\n- Send SMS \"EPFOHO UAN\" to 7738299899\n\n4. SMS Service:\n- Send SMS \"BALANCE UAN LAST 4 DIGITS OF MEMBER ID\" to 7738299899\n\n5. Offline Methods:\n- Visit EPFO regional office\n- Check employer's salary slip\n- Contact your company's HR department\n\n6. Call EPFO helpline:\n- Dial 1800-118-005\n\nNote: You must have an activated UAN and registered mobile number to access most online services.",
